<subSubSection id="12A1C4B92A4ED848FF3E7B6A1FECB2BF" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph id="5A0497322A4ED848FF3E7B6A1E60B4CF" blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FF3E7B6A1E99B45B" bold="true" box="[151,410,613,638]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: With the character states of Asiatic 
<taxonomicName id="9DBBECB12A4ED848FC927B6A1C9FB45B" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[827,924,613,638]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FC927B6A1C9FB45B" box="[827,924,613,638]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the widest sense, see above), restricted as follows: abdominal sternum VII with four or more setae in males (two or more on each side), six or more setae in females (three or more on each side); sternum VII notched in males (
<figureCitation id="C2808BB72A4ED848FC7D7BA21B40B4E3" box="[980,1091,685,710]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1664,1686]" captionTargetBox="[216,1350,195,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[216,1350,195,1626]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 1–18. Characters of Calleida spp. 1–3 sternum VII of males: 1 C. cf. splendidula (Guangdong, China), [apex notched, one seta on each side]; 2 C. fukiensis (Fujian, China), [apex notched, two setae on each side]; 3 C. puncticollis sp. n. (Holotype, Hubei, China), [apex straight, four setae on each side]. 4–6 sternum VII of females: 4 C. cf. splendidula (Guangdong, China), [two setae on each side]; 5 C. fukiensis (Shaanxi, China), [three setae on each side]; 6 C. puncticollis sp. n. (Hubei, China), [six and seven setae on each side]. 7–9 basal three antennomeres: 7 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [with sparse additional setae]; 8 C. excelsa (Yunnan, China), [with dense additional setae]; 9 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [without additional setae]. 10 elytral shoulder, C. sultana (Yunnan, China), [humeral margins setose]. 11–14 pronotal anterior angle: 11 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [with erect setae]; 12 C. excelsa (Yunnan, China), [with erect setae]; 13 C. sultana (Yunnan, China), [with erect setae]; 14 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [without setae]. 15–18 elytral outer apical angle: 15 C. corporaali (Sabah, Malaysia), [acute, forming sharp tooth]; 16 C. borneensis sp. n. (Sabah, Malaysia), [markedly widened, not forming tooth]; 17 C. doriae (Yunnan, China), [slightly widened]; 18 C. gressittiana sp. n. (Holotype), [completely round, not widened]." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1302715/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">figs. 2, 5</figureCitation>
); endophallus with two short copulatory pieces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5A0497322A4ED848FF6E7BFA1CA1B573" blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FF6E7BFA1E87B52B" bold="true" box="[199,388,757,782]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Taxonomic note</emphasis>
: Two already described species, 
<taxonomicName id="9DBBECB12A4ED848FD5F7BF91CDEB52B" authority="Heller" authorityName="Heller in Mindanao" authorityYear="1921" box="[758,989,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoidalis">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FD5F7BF91C93B52B" box="[758,912,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">C. discoidalis</emphasis>
Heller
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9DBBECB12A4ED848FBBD7BF91BFFB52B" authority="Jedlicka" authorityName="Jedlicka" authorityYear="1953" box="[1044,1276,757,782]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fukiensis">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FBBD7BF91B95B52B" box="[1044,1174,757,782]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">C. fukiensis</emphasis>
Jedlička
</taxonomicName>
, are attributed to this group, and several new species will be described in our next contribution (Shi &amp; Casale, submitted). Species of this group are distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="22ACD7A22A4ED848FE5B7A321D3BB573" box="[498,568,829,854]" name="China" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="22ACD7A22A4ED848FDEA7A311D7FB570" box="[579,636,830,853]" name="Laos" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="22ACD7A22A4ED848FD2E7A321DE5B573" box="[647,742,829,854]" name="Vietnam" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="22ACD7A22A4ED848FCB57A321C9DB573" box="[796,926,829,854]" name="Philippines" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5A0497322A4ED848FF6E7A6E1C24B20B" blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This species group is very probably not monophyletic, and relationships amongst species are unclear. In species of this group the only similarity is the presence of two short copulatory pieces in endophallus, a character common with many Asiatic, African and Madagascan 
<taxonomicName id="9DBBECB12A4ED848FCA17AA61C6BB5E7" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[776,872,937,962]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FCA17AA61C6BB5E7" box="[776,872,937,962]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The group is so far defined by one only external morphological feature (abdominal sternum VII multisetose), which could be demonstrated as not synapomorphic in the Asiatic species: in fact, this character is also present in 
<taxonomicName id="9DBBECB12A4ED848FBAC7AFE1B65B22F" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[1029,1126,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FBAC7AFE1B65B22F" box="[1029,1126,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Calleida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of several different groups in Africa, Madagascar and the Neotropical Region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5A0497322A4ED848FF6E7D361FECB2BF" blockId="15.[151,1436,613,1178]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Nevertheless, at moment the multiple setation of the abdominal sternum VII is a valid diagnostic feature able to isolate this “group of convenience” from all other species of Asia (except the 
<taxonomicName id="9DBBECB12A4ED848FBB77D521BA2B253" box="[1054,1185,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calleida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticollis">
<emphasis id="68CF4B202A4ED848FBB77D521BA2B253" box="[1054,1185,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">puncticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, treated before).
</paragraph>
